+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XqeyFXMJ7nLQGyf69mcNwJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NyoXJ3d3kdw1bEbMofLTdm","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-constraint-scheduler.md","content":"# Constraint-Based Event Scheduler Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a constraint-based event scheduler that assigns events to rooms within a time window, respecting capacity limits, prerequisite ordering, and room preferences, maximizing the number of events scheduled.\n\n**Architecture:** Define TypeScript interfaces for Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult. Implement a `schedule()` function that: (1) validates the prerequisite DAG for cycles via topological sort, (2) uses a backtracking/greedy algorithm to assign events to rooms maximizing scheduled count, (3) respects capacity, time window, gap, prerequisite, and preference constraints.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.0, ESLint, Node16 modules\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Define TypeScript Interfaces\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Create type definitions**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Event {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  duration: number;\n  attendees?: number;\n  prerequisites?: string[];\n  preferredRoom?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Room {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  capacity: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ScheduleOptions {\n  startTime: number;\n  endTime: number;\n  gap?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface Assignment {\n  eventId: string;\n  roomId: string;\n  startTime: number;\n  endTime: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ScheduleResult {\n  assignments: Assignment[];\n  unscheduled: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create entry point**\n\nCreate `src/index.ts` that re-exports from types and will later export the schedule function.\n\n```typescript\nexport type { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 3: Verify build**\n\nRun: `npm run build`\nExpected: SUCCESS, no errors\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Cycle Detection Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/scheduler.ts` (stub)\n- Create: `tests/cycle-detection.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write stub scheduler**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, ScheduleResult } from './types.js';\n\nexport function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult {\n  throw new Error('Not implemented');\n}\n```\n\nUpdate `src/index.ts` to export the schedule function:\n```typescript\nexport type { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult } from './types.js';\nexport { schedule } from './scheduler.js';\n```\n\n**Step 2: Write failing tests for cycle detection**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { schedule } from '../src/index.js';\n\ndescribe('cycle detection', () => {\n  const rooms = [{ id: 'r1', name: 'Room 1', capacity: 10 }];\n  const options = { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020 };\n\n  it('throws on self-referencing prerequisite', () => {\n    const events = [{ id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['a'] }];\n    expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, options)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('throws on two-event cycle', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['b'] },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['a'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, options)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('throws on three-event cycle', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['c'] },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['a'] },\n      { id: 'c', name: 'C', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['b'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, options)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('does not throw for valid DAG', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 30 },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['a'] },\n      { id: 'c', name: 'C', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['a', 'b'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, options)).not.toThrow();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: FAIL (Not implemented)\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement Cycle Detection + Topological Sort\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/scheduler.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Implement topological sort with cycle detection**\n\nIn `src/scheduler.ts`, implement Kahn's algorithm for topological sort that throws on cycles:\n\n```typescript\nfunction topologicalSort(events: Event[]): string[] {\n  const graph = new Map<string, string[]>();\n  const inDegree = new Map<string, number>();\n\n  for (const event of events) {\n    graph.set(event.id, []);\n    inDegree.set(event.id, 0);\n  }\n\n  for (const event of events) {\n    if (event.prerequisites) {\n      for (const prereq of event.prerequisites) {\n        if (!graph.has(prereq)) {\n          throw new Error(`Prerequisite cycle detected`);\n        }\n        graph.get(prereq)!.push(event.id);\n        inDegree.set(event.id, (inDegree.get(event.id) || 0) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const queue: string[] = [];\n  for (const [id, degree] of inDegree) {\n    if (degree === 0) queue.push(id);\n  }\n\n  const sorted: string[] = [];\n  while (queue.length > 0) {\n    const id = queue.shift()!;\n    sorted.push(id);\n    for (const neighbor of graph.get(id) || []) {\n      const newDegree = inDegree.get(neighbor)! - 1;\n      inDegree.set(neighbor, newDegree);\n      if (newDegree === 0) queue.push(neighbor);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (sorted.length !== events.length) {\n    throw new Error('Prerequisite cycle detected');\n  }\n\n  return sorted;\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the `schedule` function to call topologicalSort and return empty result:\n\n```typescript\nexport function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult {\n  const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n  return { assignments: [], unscheduled: events.map(e => e.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All cycle detection tests PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Basic Scheduling Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/basic-scheduling.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests for basic scheduling**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { schedule } from '../src/index.js';\n\ndescribe('basic scheduling', () => {\n  const rooms = [{ id: 'r1', name: 'Room 1', capacity: 10 }];\n  const options = { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020 };\n\n  it('schedules a single event', () => {\n    const events = [{ id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60 }];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, options);\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n    expect(result.assignments[0].eventId).toBe('a');\n    expect(result.assignments[0].roomId).toBe('r1');\n    expect(result.assignments[0].startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(540);\n    expect(result.assignments[0].endTime).toBeLessThanOrEqual(1020);\n    expect(result.assignments[0].endTime - result.assignments[0].startTime).toBe(60);\n  });\n\n  it('schedules multiple events in same room with gap', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60 },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 60 },\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, options);\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n    expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n    const a = result.assignments.find(x => x.eventId === 'a')!;\n    const b = result.assignments.find(x => x.eventId === 'b')!;\n    // Must have at least 15 min gap (default)\n    const [first, second] = a.startTime < b.startTime ? [a, b] : [b, a];\n    expect(second.startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(first.endTime + 15);\n  });\n\n  it('respects custom gap', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60 },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 60 },\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020, gap: 30 });\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n    const a = result.assignments.find(x => x.eventId === 'a')!;\n    const b = result.assignments.find(x => x.eventId === 'b')!;\n    const [first, second] = a.startTime < b.startTime ? [a, b] : [b, a];\n    expect(second.startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(first.endTime + 30);\n  });\n\n  it('marks events as unscheduled when they dont fit', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 480 }, // 8 hours - fills entire day\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 60 },  // won't fit with gap\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, options);\n    // At least one should be scheduled\n    expect(result.assignments.length + result.unscheduled.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('handles zero-gap scheduling', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60 },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 60 },\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, { startTime: 540, endTime: 660, gap: 0 });\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n    expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: basic scheduling tests FAIL\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Implement Core Scheduling Algorithm\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/scheduler.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Implement the scheduling algorithm**\n\nThe core algorithm:\n1. Topological sort events (with cycle detection)\n2. Build event map for quick lookup\n3. For each event in topological order, try to assign it to rooms (preferred first)\n4. Find earliest available slot in each room respecting prerequisites and gaps\n5. Use backtracking to maximize scheduled events\n\n```typescript\nexport function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult {\n  const gap = options.gap ?? 15;\n\n  // Validate and topologically sort\n  const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n\n  const eventMap = new Map<string, Event>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    eventMap.set(event.id, event);\n  }\n\n  // Track room schedules: roomId -> list of {start, end}\n  const roomSchedules = new Map<string, { start: number; end: number }[]>();\n  for (const room of rooms) {\n    roomSchedules.set(room.id, []);\n  }\n\n  const assignments: Assignment[] = [];\n  const assignmentMap = new Map<string, Assignment>();\n  const unscheduled: string[] = [];\n\n  for (const eventId of sorted) {\n    const event = eventMap.get(eventId)!;\n    const attendees = event.attendees ?? 1;\n\n    // Determine earliest start based on prerequisites\n    let earliestStart = options.startTime;\n    if (event.prerequisites) {\n      for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n        const prereqAssignment = assignmentMap.get(prereqId);\n        if (!prereqAssignment) {\n          // Prerequisite not scheduled - can't schedule this event\n          earliestStart = Infinity;\n          break;\n        }\n        earliestStart = Math.max(earliestStart, prereqAssignment.endTime + gap);\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (earliestStart === Infinity || earliestStart + event.duration > options.endTime) {\n      unscheduled.push(eventId);\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Sort rooms: preferred room first, then by capacity (smallest sufficient first)\n    const eligibleRooms = rooms\n      .filter(r => r.capacity >= attendees)\n      .sort((a, b) => {\n        if (event.preferredRoom === a.id) return -1;\n        if (event.preferredRoom === b.id) return 1;\n        return a.capacity - b.capacity;\n      });\n\n    let bestAssignment: Assignment | null = null;\n\n    for (const room of eligibleRooms) {\n      const slots = roomSchedules.get(room.id)!;\n      const startTime = findEarliestSlot(slots, earliestStart, event.duration, gap, options.endTime);\n\n      if (startTime !== null) {\n        if (!bestAssignment || startTime < bestAssignment.startTime ||\n            (startTime === bestAssignment.startTime && event.preferredRoom === room.id)) {\n          bestAssignment = {\n            eventId,\n            roomId: room.id,\n            startTime,\n            endTime: startTime + event.duration,\n          };\n          // If this is the preferred room and it works, use it\n          if (event.preferredRoom === room.id) break;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (bestAssignment) {\n      assignments.push(bestAssignment);\n      assignmentMap.set(eventId, bestAssignment);\n      const slots = roomSchedules.get(bestAssignment.roomId)!;\n      slots.push({ start: bestAssignment.startTime, end: bestAssignment.endTime });\n      slots.sort((a, b) => a.start - b.start);\n    } else {\n      unscheduled.push(eventId);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { assignments, unscheduled };\n}\n\nfunction findEarliestSlot(\n  slots: { start: number; end: number }[],\n  earliestStart: number,\n  duration: number,\n  gap: number,\n  endTime: number,\n): number | null {\n  if (slots.length === 0) {\n    if (earliestStart + duration <= endTime) return earliestStart;\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // Try before first slot\n  if (earliestStart + duration + gap <= slots[0].start ||\n      (slots.length === 0)) {\n    if (earliestStart + duration <= endTime) {\n      // Check there's enough gap before the first slot\n      if (earliestStart + duration + gap <= slots[0].start || earliestStart + duration <= slots[0].start) {\n        if (earliestStart + duration + gap <= slots[0].start) {\n          return earliestStart;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Try between slots and after last slot\n  let candidateStart = earliestStart;\n  for (let i = 0; i < slots.length; i++) {\n    // candidateStart must be after this slot ends + gap\n    if (candidateStart < slots[i].end + gap) {\n      candidateStart = slots[i].end + gap;\n    }\n\n    // Check if fits before next slot (or end of day)\n    const nextStart = i + 1 < slots.length ? slots[i + 1].start : endTime + gap;\n    if (candidateStart + duration + gap <= nextStart || (i + 1 >= slots.length && candidateStart + duration <= endTime)) {\n      if (candidateStart + duration <= endTime) {\n        return candidateStart;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Capacity and Room Constraint Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/capacity.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write capacity/room tests**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { schedule } from '../src/index.js';\n\ndescribe('capacity constraints', () => {\n  it('rejects event exceeding room capacity', () => {\n    const events = [{ id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60, attendees: 50 }];\n    const rooms = [{ id: 'r1', name: 'Room 1', capacity: 10 }];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020 });\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(0);\n    expect(result.unscheduled).toEqual(['a']);\n  });\n\n  it('assigns event to room with sufficient capacity', () => {\n    const events = [{ id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 60, attendees: 15 }];\n    const rooms = [\n      { id: 'r1', name: 'Small', capacity: 10 },\n      { id: 'r2', name: 'Large', capacity: 20 },\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, rooms, { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020 });\n    expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(result.assignments[0].roomId).toBe('r2');\n  });\n\n  it('uses multiple rooms for concurrent events', () => {\n    const events = [\n      { id: 'a', name: 'A', duration: 120 },\n      { id: 'b', name: 'B', duration: 120 },\n    ];\n    const rooms = [\n      { id: 'r1', name: 'Room 1', capacity: 10 },\n      { id: 'r2', name: 'Room 2', capacity: 10 },\n    ];\n    const result = schedule(events, roo